#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:875
msgid "## Code Mining"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:877
msgid "Code Mining shows inline annotations in the text editor that are not part of the text itself, but derived from its contents. It can be very helpful to leverage code minings for example to show inferred types, parameter names for literals and other kind of meta information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:879
msgid "Code minings come in two flavors: \"header annotations\" are printed in a separate line above the mined text, \"inline annotations\" are shown in-line. The following screenshot shows both flavors:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:881
msgid "![](images/code_mining.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:883
msgid "To enable code mining, the `org.eclipse.xtext.xtext.generator.ui.codemining.CodeMiningFragment` has to be integrated in the `language` section of the MWE2 file as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:885
msgid ""
"```mwe2\n"
"fragment = org.eclipse.xtext.xtext.generator.ui.codemining.CodeMiningFragment {}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:889
msgid "With execution of the generator a stub class `<LanguageName>CodeMiningProvider` is created in the `.codemining` sub-package of the UI plugin. Furthermore the provider is registered to the `org.eclipse.ui.workbench.texteditor.codeMiningProviders` extension point in the `plugin.xml`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:891
msgid "The following class `MyDslCodeMiningProvider` shows a simple example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:893
msgid ""
"```java\n"
"public class MyDslCodeMiningProvider extends AbstractXtextCodeMiningProvider {\n"
"\t@Override\n"
"\tprotected void createCodeMinings(IDocument document, XtextResource resource, CancelIndicator indicator,\n"
"\t\tIAcceptor<ICodeMining> acceptor) throws BadLocationException {"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:899
msgid "\t\tacceptor.accept(createNewLineHeaderCodeMining(1, document, \"header annotation\"));"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:901
msgid ""
"\t\tacceptor.accept(createNewLineContentCodeMining(5, \" inline annotation \"));\n"
"\t}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:907
msgid "Clients have to implement the `createCodeMinings()` method, compute text and position of meta information that should be presented in the text editor. Finally instances of `ICodeMining` are created with that information and passed to the `acceptor`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:909
msgid "The base class `AbstractXtextCodeMiningProvider` provides some factory methods for creating `ICodeMining` instances for convenience. Use `createNewLineHeaderCodeMining()` and `createNewLineContentCodeMining()` for that purpose."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../documentation/310_eclipse_support.md:911
msgid "For an implementation reference, have a look at the Xtext Domainmodel example."
msgstr ""

